Thousands of troops were deployed to Baluchistan after a rocket attack on a gas plant killed eight people.
Tribal rebels clashed with paramilitary forces, resulting in casualties and injuries.
The rebels claimed that up to 50 tribesmen were killed, but officials disputed this.
The violence escalated following a rape incident at the gas field.
Residents fled as clashes intensified, with bomb blasts and power outages reported.
The situation remains tense as government forces and tribal groups engage in fierce battles, leading to casualties on both sides.
